The paper deals with wireless sensor networks and their coverage problems, which are typically studied in the computer networks and communications (cs.NI) sub-category. The use of discrete algorithms and optimization techniques suggests that the paper may also belong to the data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category. The paper also deals with control systems (cs.SY) and robotics (cs.RO) as it proposes algorithms for sensor selection and gap mending. Finally, the use of information theory concepts in the paper suggests that it may also belong to the information theory (cs.IT) sub-category.
